Introduction

A.C.E is a five-member boy group under Beat Interactive and Swing Entertainment. They debuted on May 23, 2017, with their first single album "Cactus".

The members of A.C.E are Lee Donghun, Wow, Park Junhee, Kim Byeongkwan, and Kang Yuchan.

The group name "A.C.E" stands for "Adventure Calling Emotions".

On March 31, 2025, Beat Interactive’s exclusive contract with A.C.E will officially conclude, marking the end of their decade-long journey together. After thorough discussions, both parties have mutually agreed not to renew the contract, allowing A.C.E to continue their activities freely under their group name without any conditions. Beat Interactive expresses deep gratitude to A.C.E and their fans, Choice, for the years of shared trust, growth, and success. While parting is bittersweet, the company remains supportive of A.C.E’s future endeavors and looks forward to cheering them on as fans.
